A primary alcohol resulting from the cleavage of the phosphate group of the prodrug PF-07304814. It is an inhibitor of SARS-CoV-1 and -2 main protease (3CLpro) and exhibits potent in vitro antiviral activity.

An amino tetrasaccharide comprising a chain of 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronic acid, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and alpha-D-mannose residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4) and (1->2).
A branched amino heptasaccharide consisting of three sialyl residues, two galactose residues, one N-acetylglucosamine and a glucose residue at the reducing end.

A methyl ketone that is 4-phenylbutan-2-one in which the phenyl ring is substituted at positions 3 and 4 by ethoxy and hydroxy groups, respectively. It is a preservative with antimicrobial activity and a good safety profile that has been approved for use in cosmetics. It is structurally similar to zingerone, a phytochemical found in the root of the ginger plant Zingiber officinale.
A xanthene dye that is highly fluorescent and commonly used as a fluorescent tracer.
A spiro compound that is 1,8-dimethyl-4-(prop-1-en-2-yl)spiro[4.5]decane that has been dehydrogenated to introduce a double bond at position 8-9 (the 1R,4S,5R isomer).
